      "id": 10581072,
      "is_internal": false,
      "editable": false,
      "type": "Activities::Comment",
      "message": "Hi @hogarth45,\nThanks again for your report! \nWe’re awarding a $500 bounty for this issue. Please find below our rationale generated using our [CVSS calculator](https://shopify.github.io/appsec/cvss_calculator/).\n\nAttack Complexity is high since this relies on the store owner only checking the Role and not checking any individual employee with that role and noticing the discrepancy.\nPrivileges Required is high since the attacker needs Users permission in order to create the role.\n\n## Base Score CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N 2.2\n## Environment: Core\n\n#### Attack Complexity: H\n* Specific conditions or measurable effort to exploit?: Yes\n\n#### Privileges Required: H\n* Requires privileged account (not self-registered)?: Yes\n* Does the attacker need extensive permissions?: Yes\n\n#### User Interaction: N\n* Requires victim to perform some action during exploit?: No\n\n#### Scope: U\n* Can the attacker impact a separate service?: No\n\n#### Confidentiality: N\n* How much data could be accessed?: None\n\n#### Integrity: L\n* How much data could be changed?: Some\n* How much of Shopify is impacted?: Some\n\n#### Availability: N\n* Level of disruption to network service?: None\n",
      "automated_response": false,
